p:
One-way or two-way ANOVA were, respectively used for comparisons of more than two groups with single or multiple time points, followed by a Tukey's or Dunnett's post-test to adjust for multiple comparisons. All statistical analyses were performed in GraphPad Prism 7.0. The asterisks shown in the figures refer to the level of significance, 
 *
 p ≤ 0.05; 
 **
 p ≤ 0.01; 
 ***
 p ≤ 0.001; 
 ****
 p ≤ 0.0001. Serum analysis and viral titer quantification were analyzed in an un-blinded manner.
